26/09/2003
BELGRADE, Serbia-Montenegro -- Serbian Prime Minister Zoran Zivkovic makes a one-day official visit to Bulgaria on Friday (26 September), the first by a Serbian cabinet head. During the visit to Sofia, Zivkovic and his Bulgarian counterpart, Simeon Saxe-Coburg, are to sign a number of agreements, including a joint document on construction of a Sofia-Nis highway and railway. They will also sign a memorandum of co-operation in the fight against organised crime, drugs and human trafficking, and other illegal activities.
In other news, Serbia-Montenegro President Svetozar Marovic met Thursday with UN Secretary General Kofi Annan in New York. They discussed dialogue scheduled to begin between Belgrade and Pristina in October, and agreed that there are problems with implementing UN Security Council Resolution 1244 on Kosovo. (Trud, Sega, 24 Chassa - 26/09/03; BNT, BTA, B92 - 25/09/03)
